 diachronic development of Greek vocabulary. The methodology employed in this study is interdisciplinary. It involves critical and comparative examination of the written sources (papyri, literary passages, inscriptions, tituli picti) and the archaeological artefacts, and allows the revaluation of the entire material at our disposal. This interdisciplinary approach provides a useful tool for the study of the language and material culture of the Graeco-Roman world.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn Italian.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aArchäologie. 0aGreek languagevTerminology. 0aGreek languagexTerminologyxTerminology. 0aGreek languagexTerminology. 0aManuscripts, Greek (Papyri). 0aPapyrologie. 0aVasen /Antike. 0aVases, Greek. 4aArchäologie. 4aPapyrologie. 4aVasen /Antike. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / General.2bisacsh  aArchaeology.  aantique vases.  apapyrology.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2016 Part 1z978311076250108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2016z9783110485097oZDB-23-DGD0 cEPUBz97831104580220 cprintz978311045609740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311045842840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110458428423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110458428/original  a978-3-11-070100-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  a978-3-11-076250-1  DG Plus DeG Package 2016 Part 1b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGDb2016  aZDB-23-DGGb2016